// SPEC §7.2 (v0.7): the gpu namespace. The `gpu` cargo feature may or may
// not be compiled in, and a real adapter may or may not exist where the
// suite runs — so this test pins only build-independent behavior.
// (`Bytes` itself is pinned separately in bytes_basics.fable.)

// adapter_info() always returns a non-empty description: "gpu support not
// compiled in", "no adapter", or the adapter's "<name> (<backend>)".
println(gpu.adapter_info().len() > 0);       //? expect: true

// run() fails without a working GPU path (feature off, or no adapter); and
// if a GPU is genuinely available, gpu.available() is true (the empty shader
// would error anyway — no `main` entry point).
println(gpu.run("", bytes(4), 4, 1, 1, 1).is_err() || gpu.available());  //? expect: true

// Argument validation errors are Err values (never panics) and identical in
// both builds: they are checked before any device work.
println(gpu.run("", bytes(4), 0, 1, 1, 1).unwrap_err());   //? expect: gpu.run: out_len must be positive
println(gpu.run("", bytes(4), 6, 1, 1, 1).unwrap_err());   //? expect: gpu.run: out_len must be a multiple of 4 bytes, got 6
println(gpu.run("", bytes(4), 4, 0, 1, 1).unwrap_err());   //? expect: gpu.run: workgroup count x must be in 1..=65535, got 0
println(gpu.run("", bytes(0), 4, 1, 1, 1).unwrap_err());   //? expect: gpu.run: input must not be empty (storage buffers cannot be zero-sized)
println(gpu.run("", bytes(6), 4, 1, 1, 1).unwrap_err());   //? expect: gpu.run: input length must be a multiple of 4 bytes, got 6
